🚀 Frontend Interview Series — Part 3
(Advanced Angular interview questions | 2–4 years experience)
These are the questions where interviewers start checking whether you’ve worked on real projects 😅
1️⃣ Explain the Angular component lifecycle. Which hooks do you use most often?
2️⃣ When would you use ngOnInit() vs ngAfterViewInit()?
3️⃣ What causes memory leaks in Angular applications?
4️⃣ What happens if you don’t unsubscribe from Observables? How do you prevent it?
5️⃣ Explain the difference between switchMap, mergeMap, concatMap, and exhaustMap.
6️⃣ In what scenario would you use switchMap()?
7️⃣ Reactive Forms vs Template-driven Forms — when would you choose each?
8️⃣ How do you create custom validators in Angular?
9️⃣ How do Angular Route Guards work?
🔟 Tricky Angular Question 👇
You have:
ngOnInit() {
 console.log('Init');
}

ngAfterViewInit() {
 console.log('After View');
}
👉 Which runs first, and why? 🤔
